A Star Point Pattern (41)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b White to Play.\b0
\par White pushes up at 1 and it is natural for black to resist by pushing through with 2.
\par
\par In response to white defending at 3, it is a little strange for black to cut on this side with 4.
\par
\par Where should white answer it?
\par }
