Diagram 4 (Not Enough For Black)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par When white plays dansu on the black \'a1\'e3 stone with 1, if black hanes over the head of the two white stones with 2 attempting to seal white in, it's a good move for white to calmly extend to 3. This result is not good enough for black.
\par
\par If black next plays at 4, white hanes at W5 and there is a break in black's center influence.
\par
\par Black's initial move, cutting white's group with \'a1\'e3 was not good.
\par }
